<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
    
        <div class="govspeak">
<h3 id="simpson-v-unite-the-union-262728-january-2021">Simpson v Unite the union: 26/27/28 January 2021</h3>

<p>The applicant made four complaints under 108A (1) of the Trade Union and Labour Relations (Consolidation) Act 1992. Complaints 1-3 are that the union breached its rules relating to the disciplinary process. Complaint four is with regards to the applicant not being given access to the union’s accounting records and therefore breaching Section 30(2) of the Act.</p>

<p>The case will be heard remotely using Zoom videoconferencing facilities.  If you wish to join the hearing via Zoom, please contact the Certification Office by email info@certoffice.org or by calling 0330 109 3609.</p>

<h3 id="kidd-v-musicians-union--cancelled">Kidd v Musicians’ Union:  Cancelled</h3>

<p>The applicant made a complaint under 108A (1) of the Trade Union and Labour Relations (Consolidation) Act 1992 that the union breached its rule with regards to the eligibility criteria for the election of the General Secretary.</p>

<h3 id="hussain-v-communication-workers-union-postponed-until-further-notice">Hussain v Communication Workers Union: Postponed until further notice</h3>

<p>The applicant made five complaints that the Union breached its rules relating to elections at the South East No.5 Branch of the Union.  The Certification Officer struck out complaints 2-5.  Complaint 1 is to be heard.</p>

<hr></hr>
<p>If you have a disability and need help attending a hearing, please contact the Certification Office (info@certoffice.org / 0330 109 3602) to discuss any reasonable adjustment you need.</p>
</div>

